HEADWORD: Areolation
<hw>A`re*o*la"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Division into areol⟦ae⟧.</def> <rj><au>Dana.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any small space, bounded by some part different in
color or structure, as the spaces bounded by the nervures of the wings
of insects, or those by the veins of leaves; an areola.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Areole</ent>⟦br⟧
